caption: Great neighborhood bar with AMAZING food.

This neighborhood spot is second to none. Sam & crew are seriously the greatest and will make sure you have the best time whether you're in for a beer or dinner. This will instantly be your go-to bar after one sip.

Wonderful experience at Aberdeen Tap!!! The server and bartender were excellent! I was directed to a table outside next to a firepit right away, and they took our orders immediately! Everyone was safe and courteous, the food was excellent, and I was given a great recommendation for cocktails. Definitely recommend coming here now!
This is my absolutely favorite place! The best bar food you’ll have, excellent beer and spirit selection, great staff, and a nice relaxed atmosphere. Try the pulled pork nachos!
Fantastic restaurant I have ever been to.  Amazing service.
Super cute spot with an igloo and fire pit very cozy
First, Amazing wings. Second, SINGLE TABLE TENTS make me feel so much better about covid safety.

Best place to drink outdoors in the city!
Love the  guys that work here, amazing food, service, and location.  Support them during the pandemic by ordering delivery / pickup from here, you will not be disappointed.

The best!

Aberdeen Tap is local to me, but somehow I'd never been here to eat or drink. Was out for a walk last week and passed Aberdeen Tap. Lots of outdoor seating that is socially distanced. The food (pub food) looked great. The very next day I ordered takeout. I had the Aberdeen Burger with fries. It was excellent. When ordering online you specify how you want your burger cooked and and additions. My burger was cooked perfectly. Fries were crispy and fresh. I would definitely recommend Aberdeen Tap.
Definitely try the fried mac and cheese!
Excellent food, beverages & service
The best neighborhood bar in Chicago. That's it. That's the review.
We always have a great time sitting on the patio because we can bring our pitbull. The shrimp tacos are amazing. Our 3-year-old is a big fan of the disco ball inside. The staff is great!
Friendly staff and good beer on tap, what more can you ask for!

This place has amazing food. You really have to try these wings. I suggest the jerk and Carolina gold. But the star is the pepper pork banger. Simply amazing. Well done Aberdeen Tap.

An absolute classic for any Chicago E-skateborder. We come here probably about once a month at least to grab a drink and some grub while we charge. The staff is always friendly and we have never had an issue with charging our boards. Definitely one of my favorite bars in Chicago!

Wish I got some photos to share but I was too wrapped up In the amazing burger I had on top of awesome service / friendly staff. The daily specials are really good for west loop area and the Wednesday $5 burger and fries deal was mouth watering. Can’t wait to come back!
Great bar. Beware bc I come in hot and will spend cash on Touch Tunes to control the jams!
Stumbled on this place in accident! Friendly staff, great music and great food!

Good drinks and service.  Staff is always friendly.  A good alternative to the way more expensive and frankly overbearing bars in the area.  This place is good for a beer or two and is not a meat market.

Awesome staff. Fantastic beer selection. Great food. Delicious burgers. My favorite neighborhood spot. We get burgers/food here a couple times a month.

Awesome staff (who tend to have great music going when they're running it), good bar food--especially their fries, Buffalo wings and the duck confit grinder. Menu could use an overhaul. But this is a favorite and was my neighborhood local for years before I moved away!

There are a myriad of delicious beers to choose from. The wings are decent and the ambiance is chill. After work or in the neighborhood, this bar is always good for a pint or two. Aberdeen Tap is a classic Chicago bar if there ever was one.

A laid back neighborhood bar with room in the back for large groups, plenty of screens to watch a game. Friendly staff that crush it even when it’s slammed during a big game, GREAT FOOD- yes it’s bar food like wings and the like but perfectly prepared and very flavorful. You need to treat yourself to a medium-rare burger with merkts cheese and feel fat and midwestern in the best way.
I had no idea that the food here is this great. Absolutely loved the flavors and the wide variety of food to choose from. Great hangout for friends

Karl was slammed with a full bar by himself. We didnt mind, he was thankful we were patient and our food came out right away. The shortrib grinder is amazing. Love this spot for comforting hangover food, price points and the cozy neighborhood feel.

This place was great! We had no idea how good the food would be, but WOW they really did nail it. They have a great selection of beers and appetizers. But the star if the show were the wings! Perfectly cooked, and excellent sauces. Cant ask for more for wings and beers!
always a solid choice for drinks and pub grub

I've been to a few bars before and this is world's greater than every other one. I had half a beer before I was laughing and talking with complete strangers. It was an amazing time and I wish were staying in Chicago for more than 24 hours. The beer was cold and the waitstaff were friendly as hell and quick too. Now you might be thinking that's the end of this rave reviews but no. The food. Oh my god the food. Get the Cubano and you will melt. I've never tasted anything this delicious. Then I realized it was just the bread and took another bite with meat and cheese and all that in it. Jesus it was delicious. I'd pay tremendous amounts of money to have another one.  In short, go to Aberdeen Tap.
Bad service

Great little place with a nice outdoor seating area and delicious food.  Will return, next time I'm in Chicago.

We had chicken wings, fries and of course beer. Nice neighborhood bar. Multicultural patrons and employees which is always a positive for me. We will be back.

This place is great. Classic pub kinda feel but a bit more I guess. Small but well planned. Outdoor seating is nice this time of year. Good drink menu fir bottled and canned. Limited draft but it rotates so that's nice. The food is delicious! I snagged some wings this time through and I was not disappointed! The breading is different and crisp. I love it. Chiliyaki is so good.

Do I "know it" I was nonchalantly asked by Google. Know it? I love it, I exclaimed exuberantly (in my head)! I almost hit a waitress in the face with my overly expressive hands and she did not even get upset. She gave me a knowing look, which lord knows I deserved, but otherwise continued on with her job. This type of service is irreplaceable. So I reiterate, I love it!!

Great neighborhood hangout with some of the best vibes in town. The food is delicious with the Mac n cheese bites, wings, and buffalo chicken banger some of my favorite items on the menu. Also, the house made ranch is a must for pretty much anything and their Bloody Mary is one of the best I’ve had with just the right amount of spice.
Great -- unique food selections with a chill atmosphere. Definitely a spot to bring a client to.

I am the Hard Rock Critic, first time here and i walked away excited and cant wait to come back.  Had the BLT with the peppercorn mayo and the slab bacon, delicious.  Great service, amazing food, friendly staff.  Amazing job guys dont stop being amazing!!!!!  Follow me on Instagram at hardrockcritic for great places and awesome pictures Instagram: @hardrockcritic

Very good food, had the best wings I've had in a long time, and a burger, done right and not too expensive especially for Chicago, service was great too, friendly atmosphere. I am a picky eater and I recommend this place.

A popular appetizer is the fried mac and cheese squares, and they do not disappoint.  They also serve Lone Star, which is awesome.  Service is always great and the environment is boisterous and fun.

This place is a real diamond in the rough. In an area filled with expensive or pretentious options, this place is comfortable, just old enough with a plentiful beer list, a menu that is not the norm (gator sausage, cevapcici, etc) but always large filling plates. I’d go here daily if I lived closer and wanted to gain weight or do some damage to my liver. Worth the walk, drive, ride.

Hidden gem just outside of river north and west loop. Great homemade food and beer selection. It has street parking available on Hubbard and I have always been able to find a spot. If you are looking for a place to meet up with an old friend, first date, or double date look no further. My guests always impressed with a visit to this hidden gem.
